&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Card Payment Delivery Associate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tipalti is seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Card Payment Delivery Associate&lt;/strong&gt; to join a growing global team dedicated to card revenue expansion. This is an early-career role that contributes significantly to the company’s growth strategy by executing and supporting card payments to suppliers. Achieving success in this position requires the timely and effective facilitation of payment processing for our customers. The Associate tracks payment statuses, manages supplier communications, and ensures precise payment instructions. This is a high-volume, strategically important role that directly impacts revenue achievement. Success in this position is essential for ensuring the accurate and timely processing of customer payments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why join Tipalti?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tipalti is the AI-powered platform for finance automation, elevating how finance teams operate in the global economy. We empower our customers to scale faster and smarter by removing the complexities of doing global business and accelerating their finance operations efficiency. Our platform provides a comprehensive suite of finance automation solutions designed for mid-market businesses across accounts payable, global payouts, procurement, employee expenses, corporate cards, supplier management, tax compliance, and treasury. Tipalti partners with leading financial institutions such as Citi, Wells Fargo, J.P. Morgan, and Visa, enabling over 5,000 global companies to efficiently and securely pay millions of suppliers and payees across 200+ countries and territories, in 120 currencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Tipalti, we pride ourselves on our collaborative culture, the quality of our product and the capabilities of our people. Tipaltians are passionate about the work they do, and keen to get the job done. Tipalti oﬀers competitive benefits, a flexible workplace, career coaching, and an environment where diverse individuals can thrive and make an impact. Our culture ensures everyone checks their egos at the door and stands ready to reach for success together.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded in Israel in 2010, Tipalti is a global business headquartered in the San Francisco Bay Area (Foster City) with offices in Tel Aviv, Plano, Toronto, Vancouver, London, Amsterdam, Tbilisi and Medellin.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you will be responsible for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contact suppliers to process payments by telephone, web portal, and/or email.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver payments accurately within service level agreements in a high-volume environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure timely authorization and settlement of payments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct daily follow-up on outstanding payments in the processing queue to ensure they are completed successfully.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and resolve payment escalations by effectively resolving conflicts with suppliers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate documentation in relevant systems throughout the payment lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with suppliers to confirm precise payment processing details.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop cross-functional skills beyond payment delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take on other responsibilities as required to support and contribute to the success of the team and drive revenue growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
