&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Product Manager - Funds Flow&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&#39;re looking for a fast-paced, dynamic, get-stuff-done environment and want to lead a strategic product domain with real impact on one of the most critical infrastructure layers in Tipalti - this is the role for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Senior Product Manager who is a true builder at heart - someone with an innovative mindset who constantly seeks better ways to solve complex infrastructure challenges.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll lead our Funds Flow domain - the backbone that enables Tipalti&#39;s entire product suite to move money across the world. This is a high-impact, platform-oriented role at the heart of our payments infrastructure, serving both internal product teams and external financial partners&amp;nbsp; (This is an Inbound PM role).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you will be responsible for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading the product strategy and roadmap for Funds Flow - including payment routing engines, Ledger architecture, and end-to-end money movement infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Defining and evolving cross-organizational APIs and platform capabilities that enable other product domains to consume Funds Flow services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working closely with two strong engineering teams to prioritize complex tasks, drive architecture decisions, and resolve edge cases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading product integrations with international banks, acquirers, and payment partners - defining requirements and aligning on technical interfaces&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partnering with Legal, Compliance, and Finance teams to ensure full regulatory alignment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using data and reconciliation analysis to identify transaction failures, optimize routing, and reduce transfer costs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translating complex financial infrastructure requirements into clear product specs and execution plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of hands-on Product Management experience in B2B SaaS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of leading platform or infrastructure products with cross-organizational impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ability to work with Engineering on complex, multi-dependency initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with financial systems, payment infrastructure, or fintech products - an advantage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with reconciliation processes, payment routing, or financial compliance - an advantage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills across technical and non-technical audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High ownership, independence, and ability to execute under tight deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent English, both written and verbal&lt;/li&gt;
