&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of modern testing approaches (shift-left, CI/CD, test pyramid)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience defining testing strategies and improving quality practices across teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience influencing design and identifying gaps early in the development lifecycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong system thinking and ability to understand cross-team dependencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to prioritize effectively and make decisions based on impact and risk&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to influence teams without direct authority&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with test automation frameworks (Selenium WebDriver, Playwright or similar) – an advantage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in backend / API testing – an advantage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with CI/CD pipelines and DevOps practices - an advantage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with a relational database - an advantage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated, detail-oriented and organized&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent problem solving and troubleshooting skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills in English (written and verbal)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
